<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="203" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1793,2036]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,151,537]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="203" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1973,1999]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along less than half of its extension. Anterolateral margin not punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with concolorous punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[220,326,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777098/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 19G</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin concolorous (
<figureCitation box="[861,967,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777098/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 19G</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with brown stripes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777098/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 19H</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[404,545,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore strongly excavated laterally, leaving visible base of the paramere and superior process of the genital cup (
<figureCitation box="[602,740,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10C–D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim strongly projected medially around base of proctiger; lateral angles strongly projected posteriorly, covering posterolateral angles in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1321,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup half-moon shaped and concave; apex reaching dorsal rim; partially visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[159,300,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere long, dorsally directed; anterior lobe broadly expanded dorsally and rounded; posterior lobe short and triangular; inner face of the stalk with low evanescent carina curved to anterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1424,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of short setae separated by broad glabrous bridge; posterior face projected caudally and ventrally, surpassing ventral rim, resembling Greek letter Omega (
<figureCitation box="[938,1074,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10B–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim projected caudally, medial excavation shallow; expansions long, narrow, apex rounded, densely setose; surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[462,567,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="203">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
