<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="204" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1652,1895]" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1652,1678]" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">Comments.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[603,801,1653,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis box="[603,801,1653,1679]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">Hypoxys boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[854,998,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[854,998,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see comments of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1206,1350,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1350,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, this species is very different from all other species in the genus. This species has a dorsal rim very projected caudally, specially the corners; the paramere and posterior face of the proctiger are remarkable (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1374,1725,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777080/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">Fig. 10B,C</figureCitation>
); and ventral rim is clearly different from 
