<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="204" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1652,1895]" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1797,1823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the posterior face of proctiger resembling the Greek Omega letter (Suf. - 
<emphasis box="[1369,1428,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="204">oides</emphasis>
: resembling, having the form of).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
